@startuml figure-3-5-sequence-supervisor-decision
title Figure 3.5 — Sequence: Supervisor decision on a submitted case report\n(approve / needs edit / redo)

skinparam dpi 150
skinparam defaultFontName Cambria
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #E7EEF2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #1F2937
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #94A3B8
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #FEF3C7
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #92400E
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEF9C3
skinparam noteBorderColor #A16207
skinparam ArrowColor #334155
skinparam ArrowFontSize 12

actor       "Supervisor"                       as Sup
participant "Browser\n(Next.js 16)"            as Browser
participant "SupervisorController\n(NestJS)"   as Ctrl
participant "SupervisorService"                as Svc
participant "PrismaService\n(5.22)"            as Prisma
database    "PostgreSQL 16"                    as DB
participant "Notifications\nService"            as Notif
actor       "Doctor\n(student)"                 as Doctor

== 1. Supervisor reviews the report queue ==

Sup     -> Browser : Open supervisor queue;\nclick Approve / Needs edit / Redo
activate Browser

Browser -> Ctrl    : POST /supervisor/reports/:id/review\nbody: { decision, note, mark?, rating? }\nheader: Authorization: Bearer <JWT>
activate Ctrl

note right of Ctrl
  @UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard) + role guard
  ValidationPipe runs class-validator on the
  ReviewReportDto (decision enum, optional note,
  mark 0-100, rating 0-5).
end note

== 2. Service opens a Prisma $transaction ==

Ctrl -> Svc : reviewReport(supervisorId, reportId, dto)
activate Svc

Svc  -> Prisma : $transaction(async (tx) => ... )
activate Prisma

Prisma -> DB : SELECT CaseReport\nWHERE id = $1\nFOR UPDATE
activate DB
DB --> Prisma : report + linked appointment + doctor + clinicCase
deactivate DB

== 3. Branch by decision ==

alt decision = APPROVE

  Prisma -> DB : UPDATE CaseReport\nSET status='REVIEWED',\n    reviewerSupervisorId=$,\n    reviewedAt=NOW(),\n    mark=$, rating=$, feedback=$
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB

  Prisma -> DB : UPDATE DoctorClinicCaseProgress\nSET status='COMPLETED',\n    completedAt=NOW(),\n    lastReportId=$\nWHERE doctorId=$ AND clinicCaseId=$
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok  -- graduation credit booked
  deactivate DB

  Svc -> Notif : create(doctorId, 'CASE_APPROVED')
  activate Notif
  Notif -> Prisma : INSERT INTO Notification
  Prisma -> DB : ...
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB
  Notif --> Svc : ok
  deactivate Notif

else decision = NEEDS_EDIT

  Prisma -> DB : UPDATE CaseReport\nSET status='NEEDS_EDIT',\n    feedback=$ (the supervisor's note)\n-- report unlocked; same patient + doctor binding stays
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB

  note right of Prisma
    DoctorClinicCaseProgress is NOT touched.
    The case stays bound to the same patient;
    the doctor edits + resubmits the report.
  end note

  Svc -> Notif : create(doctorId, 'NEEDS_EDIT', note)
  activate Notif
  Notif -> Prisma : INSERT INTO Notification
  Prisma -> DB : ...
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB
  Notif --> Svc : ok
  deactivate Notif

else decision = REDO

  Prisma -> DB : UPDATE CaseReport\nSET status='CASE_REJECTED'
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB

  Prisma -> DB : UPDATE DoctorClinicCaseProgress\nSET status='OPEN',\n    lastReportId=NULL\n-- no graduation credit awarded
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB

  Prisma -> DB : UPDATE Appointment\nSET status='CANCELLED',\n    cancelledByDoctor=false,\n    note='supervisor REDO'
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB

  note right of Prisma
    Doctor must redo the same case category
    on a DIFFERENT patient and a FRESH
    appointment. The original case is closed.
  end note

  Svc -> Notif : create(doctorId, 'REDO', note)
  activate Notif
  Notif -> Prisma : INSERT INTO Notification
  Prisma -> DB : ...
  activate DB
  DB --> Prisma : ok
  deactivate DB
  Notif --> Svc : ok
  deactivate Notif

end

Prisma --> Svc  : tx commit
deactivate Prisma
Svc    --> Ctrl : decision result
deactivate Svc
Ctrl   --> Browser : 200 OK { case, decision }
deactivate Ctrl
Browser --> Sup : success toast +\nrow disappears from queue
deactivate Browser

Notif -->> Doctor : in-app notification +\nemail summary

note over Prisma, DB
  All three branches run inside ONE Prisma $transaction (NFR-11):
  decision write + progress flip + notification all commit together,
  or none do. There is no partial state in which a doctor sees
  COMPLETED on the progress page without the supervisor's row of
  truth in CaseReport.
end note

@enduml
